narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you have a good idea of a topic you are really interested in reading and writing about, and you are self-disciplined enough, then I can't recommend it more highly.

1. have an advisor who will make time for you, approx once every two weeks 2. set hard deadlines. start writing even when you don't think you can yet. you will not regret it. 3. pick a topic before you start your semester. make sure it's something you want to do every bit of reading about. one that you want to have a million conversations with everyone under the sun about. because people will ask. 4. make sure you have a huge amount of time and energy
